'''Gonçalo Manuel Ganchinho Guedes''' ({{IPA|pt-PT|ɡõˈsalu ˈɣɛðɨʃ|lang}};{{efn-ua|In isolation, ''Guedes'' is pronounced {{IPA|pt|ˈɡɛðɨʃ|}}.}} born 29 November 1996) is a Portuguese professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[winger (association football)|winger]] or [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[La Liga]] club [[Real Sociedad]] and the [[Portugal national football team|Portugal national team]].

Guedes began his career at [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]], making his professional debut for the [[S.L. Benfica B|reserves]] in April 2014 and the first team six months later. After 11 goals in 63 matches across all competitions, winning five major trophies, he transferred to [[Paris Saint-Germain FC|Paris Saint-Germain]] for a €30&nbsp;million transfer fee in January 2017. He played only 13 matches for PSG before being loaned to [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] in September 2017, joining them on a permanent basis for a €40&nbsp;million transfer fee a year later. He played 178 games and scored 36 goals for the Spanish club, winning the [[Copa del Rey]] in [[2019 Copa del Rey Final|2019]], and signed for Wolverhampton Wanderers for £27.5&nbsp;million in 2022.

Guedes earned 57 caps for Portugal at youth level, from under-15 to [[Portugal national under-23 football team|under-23]]. He made his senior international debut in November 2015, at age 18, and played at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]. He scored the winning goal for Portugal in the [[2019 UEFA Nations League final]].

==Club career==
===Benfica===
Born in [[Benavente, Portugal|Benavente]], Guedes joined [[S.L. Benfica]]'s youth system in 2005, where he progressed to the [[S.L. Benfica Juniors|juniors team]]. On his debut at age eight, he scored all of the goals in a 5–0 win against a team of boys three years older.<ref name=hunter/> He was part of Benfica's squad in the inaugural [[UEFA Youth League]] in [[2013–14 UEFA Youth League|2013–14]], contributing to their victories over [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]], [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]], [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] en route to the final.<ref name=hunter/>

On 19 April 2014, he made his professional debut with [[S.L. Benfica B|Benfica B]] in a [[2013–14 Segunda Liga]] match against [[FC Porto B|Porto B]], playing 21 minutes of an eventual 4–1 away loss before being replaced by [[Rudinilson Silva]].{{citation needed|date=July 2025}}

On 18 October 2014, Guedes debuted for Benfica's first team at [[S.C. Covilhã|Sporting da Covilhã]] in the [[2014–15 Taça de Portugal#Third round|third round]] of [[Taça de Portugal]].<ref>[https://www.fpf.pt/Not%C3%ADcias/Not%C3%ADcia/Id/7162/Cat/727/highlight/1/caller/56/Taca-de-Portugal-Benfica-sofre-mas-segue-em-frente Taça de Portugal: Benfica sofre mas segue em frente]</ref> On 4 January 2015, he debuted in the [[Primeira Liga]] at [[F.C. Penafiel|Penafiel]] as an added-time substitute for [[Lima (footballer, born 1983)|Lima]] in a 3–0 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ligaportugal.pt/oou/jogo/20142015/primeiraliga/15/6|title=Penafiel – Benfica (Jornada 15 Primeira Liga 2014–2015) – Liga Portugal|language=pt|date=4 January 2015|publisher=[[LPFP]]|access-date=4 January 2015|archive-date=3 March 2016|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303195303/http://www.ligaportugal.pt/oou/jogo/20142015/primeiraliga/15/6|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 4 July, he won the [[2014–15 Segunda Liga]]'s [[LPFP Awards#Segunda Liga Awards|Breakthrough Player of the Year]] award.<ref name="awards 2015">{{cite web|url=http://www.ligaportugal.pt/noticias/premios-oficiais-liga-portugal-2015/|title=Prémios Oficiais Liga Portugal 2015|language=pt|trans-title=Official Awards Liga Portugal 2015|date=4 July 2015|publisher=LPFP|access-date=4 July 2015|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150704230034/http://www.ligaportugal.pt/noticias/premios-oficiais-liga-portugal-2015/|archive-date=4 July 2015 }}</ref>

On 26 September 2015, Guedes scored his first goal with Benfica in a 3–0 victory against [[F.C. Paços de Ferreira|Paços de Ferreira]] in the [[2015–16 Primeira Liga|league]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ligaportugal.pt/oou/jogo/20152016/liganos/6/2|title=Liga NOS – Jornada 6 – SL Benfica vs FC P.Ferreira|access-date=1 October 2015|archive-date=27 September 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927045159/http://www.ligaportugal.pt/oou/jogo/20152016/liganos/6/2|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 30 September, he scored his first goal in the [[UEFA Champions League]] in a victory at [[Atlético Madrid]] (2–1),<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0226-0e91f980d915-6410786351a5-1000--how-benfica-beat-atletico-madrid/|title=How Benfica beat Atlético Madrid|last=Walker|first=Joseph|date=30 September 2015|publisher=[[UEFA]]|access-date=1 October 2015}}</ref> and became the youngest Portuguese player to have scored a goal in the group stage.<ref name=hunter/> He was praised by opposing manager [[Diego Simeone]] after the match.<ref name=hunter/>

While mainly used as a right-winger at Benfica, he played some matches as a [[false 9]] center-forward due to injury to striker [[Jonas Gonçalves Oliveira|Jonas]].<ref name=hunter/>

===Paris Saint-Germain===
On 25 January 2017, Guedes joined [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] for a €30&nbsp;million transfer fee,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://web3.cmvm.pt/sdi/emitentes/docs/FR62859.pdf|title=Comunicado|date=25 January 2017|website=CMVM|publisher=[[S.L. Benfica]]|language=pt|trans-title=Announcement|access-date=25 January 2017|archive-date=11 October 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171011092935/http://web3.cmvm.pt/sdi/emitentes/docs/FR62859.pdf|url-status=dead}}</ref> signing a contract lasting until 2021. Upon signing, he said that he wanted to emulate compatriot and former PSG player [[Pauleta]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Paris Saint-Germain complete signing of Benfica's Goncalo Guedes|url=http://www.espnfc.com/story/3046114/paris-saint-germain-complete-signing-of-benficas-goncalo-guedes|access-date=9 March 2017|publisher=[[ESPN FC]]|date=25 January 2017}}</ref> PSG won a bidding war with [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] for his signature.<ref name=keen>{{cite news|title=Goncalo Guedes: Five things about 'new Ronaldo'; PSG and United keen|url=http://www.espnfc.com/team/portugal/482/blog/post/3044747/goncalo-guedes-five-things-about-new-ronaldo-psg-and-man-united-keen|access-date=9 March 2017|publisher=ESPN FC|date=23 January 2017}}</ref>

Guedes made his debut for the [[Ligue 1]] title holders four days later, replacing fellow newcomer [[Julian Draxler]] for the final three minutes of a 1–1 home draw with [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]].<ref>{{cite news|title=PSG estreia Gonçalo Guedes, Bernardo Silva salva Mónaco|trans-title=PSG give debut to Gonçalo Guedes, Bernardo Silva saves Monaco|url=http://www.maisfutebol.iol.pt/franca/paris-saint-germain/psg-estreia-goncalo-guedes-bernardo-silva-salva-monaco|access-date=9 March 2017|publisher=Mais Futebol|date=29 January 2017|language=pt}}</ref>

===Valencia===
[[File:Real Valladolid-Valencia CF, 2019-05-18 (38) - Gonçalo Guedes.jpg|thumb|left|160px|Guedes playing for [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] in May 2019]]
On 1 September 2017, Guedes was loaned to Spanish club [[Valencia CF|Valencia]] on a season-long deal.<ref>{{cite news|title=Official Statement – Gonçalo Guedes|url=http://en.valenciacf.com/ver/72852/comunicado-oficial--gon%C3alo-guedes.html|access-date=1 September 2017|publisher=Valencia CF|date=1 September 2017|archive-date=10 January 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200110160650/http://en.valenciacf.com/ver/72852/comunicado-oficial--gon%C3alo-guedes.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> The transfer was facilitated by the contacts between his agent [[Jorge Mendes]] and the owners of Valencia.<ref name="hunter" />

Guedes made his [[La Liga]] debut eight days later, replacing [[Andreas Pereira]] for the final half-hour of a goalless home draw against Atlético Madrid.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Hernández|first1=José|title=Guedes y Paulista debutaron con nota|trans-title=Guedes and Paulista make distinguished debuts|url=http://www.deportevalenciano.com/2017/09/10/guedes-paulista-debutaron-nota|access-date=3 November 2017|publisher=Deporte Valenciano|date=10 September 2017|language=es}}</ref> On 15 October, Guedes scored the first goal of his loan in a 6–3 win at [[Real Betis]], as his unbeaten team rose to second above Real Madrid.<ref>{{cite news|title=Real Betis 3–6 Valencia|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41631357|access-date=3 November 2017|work=BBC Sport|date=15 October 2017}}</ref> Six days later, he scored twice and assisted [[Santi Mina]] in a 4–0 win over [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]], the ''Che'' team's fifth consecutive victory.<ref>{{cite news|title=Guedes hace brillar al Valencia|trans-title=Guedes makes Valencia shine|url=http://cadenaser.com/ser/2017/10/21/deportes/1508600125_468275.html|access-date=3 November 2017|publisher=Cadena SER|date=21 October 2017|language=es}}</ref> He received plaudits from the international sporting press for his early-season form.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Álvarez|first1=Fernando|title=Guedes revolutionises Valencia|url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2017/10/17/59e5df3d46163f487a8b466e.html|access-date=3 November 2017|work=Marca|location=Spain|date=17 October 2017}}</ref><ref name="hunter">{{cite news|last1=Hunter|first1=Graham|title=Goncalo Guedes is playing at Valencia like the Ballon d'Or is in his future|url=http://www.espn.co.uk/football/spanish-primera-division/15/blog/post/3241179/goncalo-guedes-is-playing-at-valencia-like-the-ballon-dor-is-in-his-future|access-date=3 November 2017|publisher=ESPN|date=24 October 2017}}</ref>

On 30 August 2018, Guedes signed permanently to Valencia on a deal running until 2024, for an initial [[List of Valencia CF records and statistics|club-record]] €40&nbsp;million fee potentially including a further €17&nbsp;million; the release clause was €300&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Álvarez |first1=Fernando |title=Guedes firma con el Valencia hasta 2024 con una cláusula récord de 300 millones|trans-title=Guedes signs with Valencia until 2024 with a record clause of 300 million |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/valencia/2018/08/30/5b8839f422601dae4e8b45d8.html |access-date=26 August 2022 |work=Marca|location=Spain |date=30 August 2018 |language=Spanish}}</ref> From December until February 2019, he was sidelined with a [[pubalgia]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Álvarez |first1=Fernando |title=Guedes vuelve a una convocatoria con el Valencia tras dos meses de lesión|trans-title=Guedes returns to a Valencia matchday squad after two months injured |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/valencia/2019/02/09/5c5f123422601d895b8b4602.html |access-date=26 August 2022 |work=Marca|location=Spain |date=9 February 2019 |language=Spanish}}</ref> He played in the [[2019 Copa del Rey Final]] on 25 May, with Valencia defeating [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]] 2–1 to win the club's first honour in 11 years.<ref>{{cite news|last=Lowe|first=Sid|title=Valencia shock Barcelona in Copa del Rey final despite Messi's best efforts|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/may/25/barcelona-valencia-copa-del-rey-final-match-report|work=The Guardian|date=25 May 2019|access-date=10 June 2019}}</ref>

From October 2019 until the following February, Guedes was out with a right ankle injury.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Sanchis |first1=Nacho |title=Gonçalo Guedes vuelve a una convocatoria 122 días después|trans-title=Gonçalo Guedes returns to a matchday squad after 122 days |url=https://as.com/futbol/2020/02/03/primera/1580753061_475985.html |access-date=26 August 2022 |work=Diario AS |date=4 February 2020 |language=Spanish}}</ref> On 30 December, he was sent off for swearing at the referee in a 2–1 loss at [[Granada CF|Granada]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Martínez |first1=Jorge |title=La rajada de Guedes contra el árbitro que le costó la expulsión en el Granada-Valencia|trans-title=Guedes' criticism of the referee which cost him a sending-off in the Granada-Valencia game |url=https://www.elespanol.com/deportes/futbol/20201230/rajada-guedes-arbitro-costo-expulsion-granada-valencia/547446536_0.html |access-date=26 August 2022 |work=El Español |date=30 December 2020 |language=Spanish}}</ref> He had the most prolific season of his career in [[2021–22 La Liga|2021–22]], finishing as his team's joint top scorer alongside [[Carlos Soler (footballer)|Carlos Soler]] with 11, while also playing the most games with 36 and most minutes with over 2,500;<ref>{{cite news |title=Bordalás utilizó 34 jugadores con Guedes y Soler como goleadores|trans-title=Bordalás used 34 players with Guedes and Soler as the top scorers|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/valencia/20220522/1001809813/bordalas-utilizo-34-jugadores-guedes-soler-goleadores.html |access-date=26 August 2022 |work=Mundo Deportivo |date=22 May 2022 |language=Spanish}}</ref> this included two goals in a 4–3 win at [[Levante UD|Levante]] in the [[Valencia derby]] on 20 December.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Burgos |first1=Julián |title=Guedes reina en un derbi loco|trans-title=Guedes reigns in a crazy derby |url=https://as.com/futbol/2021/12/20/primera/1640039174_500793.html |access-date=26 August 2022 |work=Diario AS |date=20 December 2021 |language=Spanish}}</ref> In March 2022, his long-range strike against [[Athletic Bilbao]] was the decisive goal that sent his team to another Copa final.<ref>{{cite web |title=Guedes screamer sends Valencia past Athletic Club into Copa del Rey final|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report%3fgameId=631532 |date=2 March 2022|access-date=12 March 2022}}</ref>

===Wolverhampton Wanderers===
[[File:Gonçalo Guedes makes his Wolves debut (cropped).jpg|thumb|right|150px|Guedes making his [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] debut on 13 August 2022]]
On 8 August 2022, [[Premier League]] side [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] signed Guedes on a five-year deal for £27.5&nbsp;million.<ref>{{cite news |title=Goncalo Guedes: Wolves complete £27.5m signing of Portugal forward from Valencia |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62464408 |access-date=25 August 2022 |work=BBC Sport |date=8 August 2022}}</ref> He made his debut five days later as a 58th-minute substitute for [[Hwang Hee-chan]] in a goalless draw with [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]],<ref>{{cite news|last=McKenna|first=Lorraine|title=Wolverhampton Wanderers 0–0 Fulham|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62445692|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=13 August 2022|access-date=14 August 2022}}</ref> and on 20 August made his first start in a 1–0 away defeat at [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Tottenham Hotspur 1–0 Wolverhampton Wanderers|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/62529371|work=[[BBC Sport]]|last=Sutcliffe|first=Steve|date=20 August 2022|access-date=20 August 2022}}</ref>

==== Return to Benfica on loan ====
On 20 January 2023, Guedes returned to his old club Benfica on a loan for the remainder of the [[2022–23 Primeira Liga|2022–23]] season.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Gonçalo Guedes joins Benfica! |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/en-us/agora/noticias/2023/01/20/futebol-benfica-goncalo-guedes-reforca-o-benfica |access-date=2023-01-20 |website=slbenfica.pt |language=en}}</ref> The following day, in a match away at [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]], he came on as a substitute in the 64th minute and scored, sealing a 3–0 win.<ref>{{Cite web |date=21 January 2023 |title=Regresso de sonho: Gonçalo Guedes entrou e 15 minutos depois fez o golo |trans-title=Dream return: Gonçalo Guedes came on and scored 15 minutes later |url=https://www.record.pt/multimedia/videos/detalhe/regresso-de-sonho-guedes-entrou-e-15-minutos-depois-fez-o-golo |access-date=2023-08-29 |publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]] |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

On 25 February, in a match away at [[F.C. Vizela|Vizela]], Guedes got injured and had to undergo knee surgery, sidelining him for almost two months.<ref>{{Cite web |date=10 March 2023 |title=374 minutos depois, a pior notícia: Gonçalo Guedes vai ser operado ao joelho esquerdo |trans-title=374 minutes later, the worst news: Gonçalo Guedes will undergo left knee surgery |url=https://observador.pt/2023/03/10/goncalo-guedes-vai-ser-operado-ao-joelho/ |access-date=2023-08-29 |website=Observador |language=pt-PT}}</ref> However, on 21 May 2023, in a clash against [[Lisbon derby|rivals]] [[Sporting CP]], Guedes injured the same knee, requiring him to undergo surgery once again.<ref>{{Cite web |date=24 May 2023 |title=Gonçalo Guedes volta a parar e vai ser operado ao joelho esquerdo |trans-title=Gonçalo Guedes sidelined again and will undergo left knee surgery |url=https://www.ojogo.pt/futebol/1a-liga/benfica/noticias/goncalo-guedes-volta-a-parar-e-vai-ser-operado-ao-joelho-esquerdo-16411673.html |access-date=2023-08-29 |publisher=[[O Jogo]] |language=pt-PT}}</ref> That season, Benfica were crowned Primeira Liga champions, and Guedes received a medal.<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 May 2023 |title=BENFICA CAMPEÃO: há 32 jogadores com as faixas ao peito (e alguns bem improváveis) |trans-title=Benfica's champion: there are 32 players with bands on their chest (some very unlikely) |url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/benfica/benfica-campeao/benfica-campeao-ha-32-jogadores-com-as-faixas-ao-peito-e-alguns-bem-improvaveis |access-date=2023-08-29 |website=Maisfutebol |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

On 29 August 2023, Benfica announced that Guedes' loan had been extended until the end of the [[2023–24 S.L. Benfica season|2023–24 season]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=29 August 2023 |title=Gonçalo Guedes é reforço para 2023/24 |trans-title=Gonçalo Guedes is reinforcement until 2023/24 |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2023/08/29/futebol-benfica-goncalo-guedes-reforco-emprestimo |access-date=2023-08-29 |website=SL Benfica |language=pt-PT}}</ref> On 19 January 2024, Benfica and Wolverhampton Wanderers reached an agreement for the termination of Guedes' loan spell.<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 January 2024 |title=Obrigado, Gonçalo Guedes! |trans-title=Thank you, Gonçalo Guedes! |url=https://www.slbenfica.pt/pt-pt/agora/noticias/2024/01/19/futebol-benfica-goncalo-guedes-fim-do-emprestimo |access-date=20 January 2024 |publisher=S.L. Benfica |language=pt}}</ref>

==== Loan to Villarreal ====
On 19 January 2024, hours after Guedes left Benfica, Wolverhampton Wanderers sent him on another loan, this time to La Liga club [[Villarreal CF|Villarreal]], until the end of the [[2023–24 Villarreal CF season|2023–24 season]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=19 January 2024 |title=Guedes is a Yellow! |url=https://villarrealcf.es/en/guedes-is-a-yellow/ |access-date=2024-01-20 |publisher=Villarreal CF |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 20 January 2024, Guedes made his La Liga debut for the team against [[RCD Mallorca|Mallorca]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 January 2024 |title=A cruel point against RCD Mallorca (1–1) – Web Oficial del Villarreal CF |url=https://villarrealcf.es/en/a-cruel-point-against-rcd-mallorca-1-1/ |access-date= |website=Villarreal CF |language=en-GB}}</ref> On 27 January, Guedes scored his first La Liga goal for Villarreal against Barcelona at [[Estadi Olímpic Lluís Companys]], winning the game 5–3.<ref>{{Cite news |date=27 January 2024 |title=Barcelona lose eight-goal thriller to Villarreal |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68120233 |access-date=2024-01-28 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=27 January 2024 |title=Barcelona stunned as Villarreal edge eight-goal thriller |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2024/01/27/65b558b4ca47410f7a8b457f.html |access-date=2024-01-28 |website=Marca|location=Spain |language=en}}</ref>

== International career ==
[[File:Gonçalo Guedes (cropped).jpg|thumb|left|150px|Guedes with [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]]]
Guedes was first called-up by [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] first-team manager [[Fernando Santos (footballer, born 1954)|Fernando Santos]] on 6 November 2015 ahead of international friendlies against [[Russia national football team|Russia]] and [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Portugal gives Ronaldo a rest, calls up newcomers for games|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/sports/soccer/2015/11/06/portugal-gives-ronaldo-a-rest-calls-up-newcomers-for-games/75283750/|access-date=7 November 2015|agency=Associated Press|work=[[USA Today]]|date=6 November 2015}}</ref> He made his debut eight days later against the former, starting in a 1–0 loss in [[Krasnodar]],<ref>{{cite news|title=Russia 1 Portugal 0: Shirokov proves captain fantastic in Krasnodar|url=http://www.fourfourtwo.com/news/russia-1-portugal-0-shirokov-proves-captain-fantastic-krasnodar|access-date=9 March 2017|work=[[FourFourTwo]]|date=14 November 2015}}</ref> which made him the first 18-year-old to represent the nation since [[Cristiano Ronaldo]].<ref name=keen/>

On 10 November 2017, Guedes scored his first senior international goal in a 3–0 friendly win over [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]] in [[Viseu]], also assisting [[Manuel Fernandes (footballer, born 1986)|Manuel Fernandes]] earlier in the match.<ref>{{cite news|title=Guedes stars for Portugal in Ronaldo's absence|url=http://www.beinsports.com/au/friendlies/news/guedes-stars-for-portugal-in-ronaldos-absence/705224|access-date=11 November 2017|publisher=beIN Sports|date=10 November 2017}}</ref>

Guedes was named in Portugal's 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia. In the final warm-up match before the tournament, he scored twice in a 3–0 win over [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] at the [[Estádio da Luz]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Portugal 3–0 Algeria|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44373997|access-date=8 June 2018|work=BBC Sport|date=7 June 2018}}</ref>

At the [[2019 UEFA Nations League Finals]], hosted on home soil, Guedes was a substitute for [[João Félix]] in the semi-final victory over [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] but started the final at the [[Estádio do Dragão]] against the [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]], during which he scored the match's only goal.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Law |first1=Matt |title=Result: Goncalo Guedes scores winner as Portugal land UEFA Nations League title |url=https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/portugal/uefa-nations-league/result/result-guedes-scores-winner-as-portugal-land-nations-league-title_361579.html |access-date=9 June 2019 |publisher=Sports Mole |date=9 June 2019}}</ref>

In October 2022, he was named in Portugal's preliminary 55-man [[Portugal national football team|squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] in Qatar.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.record.pt/futebol/selecoes/detalhe/cmtv-revela-lista-de-pre-convocados-para-o-mundial2022-conheca-todos-os-nomes?ref=HP_DestaquesPrincipais|title=The list of pre-selected squad for the 2022 World Cup: know all the names|publisher=[[Record (Portuguese newspaper)|Record]]|access-date=31 October 2022|date=23 October 2022}}</ref>

